definitions.definition: ( pathology ) Spongy , abnormal growth , as granulation tissue formed in a wound .

main_definition: ( pathology ) Spongy , abnormal growth , as granulation tissue formed in a wound .

definitions.definition: Alternative spelling of fungee ( “ a cornmeal dish from the Caribbean , usually made with okra and served with salt fish , shellfish , or chicken ” ) .
A style of folk and popular music from the Virgin Islands , traditionally performed by bands consisting of banjo , guitar , ukulele , and washboard with various percussion instruments on rhythm .
